> routed through Montreal or Toronto then you'll save time getting your
> stuff.

I heard folks in that area get a PO box or friend in Blaine WA or other
border town to send thier stuff to, then do the cross border bit in
person, some times they get customs, sometimes it is more work than it's
worth at the border. especially if you leave the packaging where it was
delivered,  of course you didn't hear that from me ;8*]

